From 42797d719f7ffa6e3f0b05168594879d366bca86 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Rohitraj45592 <rohitraj45592@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Fri, 17 Jul 2026 08:38:38 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] feat: add Analytics page as the central performance dashboard

New route at /dashboard-v2/analytics, built with the existing
DashboardLayout, Header and the same monochrome design language used
across Overview, Career Twin, Resume Studio, Job Hub and Mock
Interview - no layout, header, colors, radius, shadows or motion
conventions changed.

16 sections per spec: hero with a monochrome bar-chart illustration
and floating growth badges, performance snapshot, weekly progress
with 6 mini bar-chart cards, resume/interview/job analytics stat
rows, a 10-skill learning analytics section, career insights,
6-category skill distribution with animated circular rings, a
monthly timeline paired with recent activity, productivity overview,
AI recommendations, placement prediction, export report actions, and
achievement badges.

Reused the shared AnimatedNumber component and the shine-sweep
keyframe already added for Career Twin/Mock Interview instead of
duplicating that logic again.

Sidebar was updated directly in this same commit (Analytics item now
links to its route) per the task's explicit instruction not to
generate a separate sidebar patch.

UI only - no backend, API, auth, or database - realistic dummy
analytics data throughout.
